summary: “I’m an orphan raised by carnies fighting with a stick and a string from the Paleolithic era...Paleolithic. I looked it up.” I...
caption:
“I’m an orphan raised by carnies fighting with a stick and a string from the Paleolithic era…Paleolithic. I looked it up.”

I had the best time doing this shoot with my good friend faithmarcialphotos, and I’m amazed at the results of her work – she is the best, no question!

to me this set is a kind of love letter or swan song for this version of the Hawkguy costume…it’s served me well, but it’s time for some updates. can you believe I’m still using the same shirt that I made three years ago? I can’t

that’s why these pictures are so special to me: if an unadulterated pro can make something that’s still a kind of work-in-progress look this good, imagine what it’ll look like once it’s been overhauled! so here’s to the future

–Hawkeye out

summary:
Wow, 100 of you have now subscribed to my AO3 account to get emails whenever I post a new story! 😱
Thank you so much for all...
body:
Wow, 100 of you have now subscribed to my AO3 account to get emails whenever I post a new story! 😱

Thank you so much for all your love and support! ❤

Writing is something that gives me so much pleasure that I would do it even if I didn’t have an audience, but the fact that you guys seemingly love to read my works as much as I love writing them makes things so much more rewarding.

Thank you for sharing this journey with me and I look forward to sharing the first chapter of my next fic with you in November! 🎉

summary:
Symbiotic by Art Ninja Tx
Spiderman was my first, and favorite, super hero as a kid. Venom....well you can't get a better worst...
body:
Symbiotic by Art Ninja Tx

Spiderman was my first, and favorite, super hero as a kid. Venom….well you can’t get a better worst enemy and cool character in one package. I always felt like the art for venom just was off minus a couple pieces that I have seen online. I really wanted to depict venom how I see him in my mind…someone…something that would bring terror to Spiderman, not just for knowing all his secrets or not for being able to be sensed by him, but by being a true monster. I really enjoyed painting this. I hope marvel/spiderman/venom fans approve. 

acrylic paint on 24" x 36 “ clayboard

Instagram: www.instagram.com/art_ninjatx/ 

Facebook: www.facebook.com/Jeuro85
